# Drathos Client - Environment Variables

# ============================================================
# CRITICAL SECURITY — DRATHOS_ENCRYPTION_KEY
# ============================================================
# This key encrypts all sensitive data stored locally (tokens, credentials, settings).
# - MUST be at least 32 characters
# - MUST be unique per deployment
# - MUST be kept secret — never commit your real key to version control
# - If lost or changed, all locally encrypted data becomes unreadable
#
# Generate a secure key:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# ============================================================
DRATHOS_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-secret-encryption-key-here-change-in-production-min-32-chars
